article.headline: Bradley 98, Md.-Eastern Shore 71
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Andrew Warren had near-perfect shooting as he scored 25 points to lead Bradley past Maryland-Eastern Shore 98-71 in the first round of the South Padre Island Invitational Sunday at Carver Arena. Bradley (2-1) took a decisive lead early, jumping out to 30-11 just 10 minutes into the game. Daniel Ruffin had 14 points and seven assists for the Braves in the game's first 18 minutes. Bradley took a comfortable 53-28 lead into halftime and shot at least 56 percent from the field, compared with 38 percent for Maryland. Sam Maniscalco had 11 points for the Braves, while David Collins added 10 points and a game-high 14 rebounds. The Hawks (1-2) got 16 points apiece out of Marc Davis and Denzel Jackson, who led the team with seven rebounds. Ed Tyson and Milutin Mirjacic both added 11. Warren made all seven of his free throw attempts, including three 3-pointers, and 8-of-9 free throws.
